The drug is a combination of three monoclonal antibodies, which are laboratory-produced proteins that can bind to specific parts of the Ebola virus and neutralize its effects.
6. Another experimental drug, called favipiravir, has also shown some promise in treating Ebola in animals. However, more research is needed to determine its effectiveness and safety in humans.

8. Early results from a clinical trial of the Johnson & Johnson Ebola vaccine showed that it was effective in preventing Ebola infection. However, further studies are needed to confirm these results.
